briefdescription.para: Deinitializes the DMAy Channelx registers to their default reset values.

parameterdescription.para: where y can be 1 or 2 to select the DMA and x can be 1 to 7 for DMA1 and 1 to 5 for DMA2 to select the DMA Channel.

briefdescription.para: Initializes the DMAy Channelx according to the specified parameters in the DMA_InitStruct.

parameterdescription.para: where y can be 1 or 2 to select the DMA and x can be 1 to 7 for DMA1 and 1 to 5 for DMA2 to select the DMA Channel.
pointer to a DMA_InitTypeDef structure that contains the configuration information for the specified DMA Channel.

briefdescription.para: Fills each DMA_InitStruct member with its default value.

parameterdescription.para: : pointer to a DMA_InitTypeDef structure which will be initialized.

briefdescription.para: Enables or disables the specified DMAy Channelx.

parameterdescription.para: where y can be 1 or 2 to select the DMA and x can be 1 to 7 for DMA1 and 1 to 5 for DMA2 to select the DMA Channel.
new state of the DMAy Channelx. This parameter can be: ENABLE or DISABLE.

briefdescription.para: Enables or disables the specified DMAy Channelx interrupts.

parameterdescription.para: where y can be 1 or 2 to select the DMA and x can be 1 to 7 for DMA1 and 1 to 5 for DMA2 to select the DMA Channel.

specifies the DMA interrupts sources to be enabled or disabled. This parameter can be any combination of the following values:
DMA_IT_TC: Transfer complete interrupt mask
DMA_IT_HT: Half transfer interrupt mask
DMA_IT_TE: Transfer error interrupt mask
new state of the specified DMA interrupts. This parameter can be: ENABLE or DISABLE.
